<subSubSection lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="72" pageId="7" pageNumber="71" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="7.[189,334,264,290]" box="[189,334,264,290]" pageId="7" pageNumber="71">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,334,264,290]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="7" pageNumber="71" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,334,264,290]" pageId="7" pageNumber="71">Description</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[189,1399,311,443]" pageId="7" pageNumber="71">
MEASUREMENTS. Male (n = 24) body length: 
<quantity box="[709,854,311,338]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.9" metricValueMax="5.1" metricValueMin="4.7" pageId="7" pageNumber="71" unit="mm" value="4.9" valueMax="5.1" valueMin="4.7">4.7–5.1 mm</quantity>
, forewing length: 3.9–4.0 mm, width between humeral angle apices: 
<quantity box="[466,615,346,373]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.8" metricValueMax="2.1" metricValueMin="1.5" pageId="7" pageNumber="71" unit="mm" value="1.8" valueMax="2.1" valueMin="1.5">1.5–2.1 mm</quantity>
, width between suprahumeral horn apices: 
<quantity box="[1148,1297,346,373]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.7" metricValueMax="1.9" metricValueMin="1.5" pageId="7" pageNumber="71" unit="mm" value="1.7" valueMax="1.9" valueMin="1.5">1.5–1.9 mm</quantity>
. Female (n = 5) body length: 
<quantity box="[438,583,381,408]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.25" metricValueMax="5.3" metricValueMin="5.2" pageId="7" pageNumber="71" unit="mm" value="5.25" valueMax="5.3" valueMin="5.2">5.2–5.3 mm</quantity>
, forewing length: 
<quantity box="[800,946,381,408]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.4" metricValueMax="4.6" metricValueMin="4.2" pageId="7" pageNumber="71" unit="mm" value="4.4" valueMax="4.6" valueMin="4.2">4.2–4.6 mm</quantity>
, width between humeral angle apices: 
<quantity box="[190,335,417,443]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.25" metricValueMax="2.3" metricValueMin="2.2" pageId="7" pageNumber="71" unit="mm" value="2.25" valueMax="2.3" valueMin="2.2">2.2–2.3 mm</quantity>
, width between suprahumeral horn apices: 
<quantity box="[842,986,416,443]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.7" metricValueMax="1.8" metricValueMin="1.6" pageId="7" pageNumber="71" unit="mm" value="1.7" valueMax="1.8" valueMin="1.6">1.6–1.8 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[189,1399,482,544]" lastBlockId="8.[188,1400,265,362]" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="72" pageId="7" pageNumber="71">
COLORATION. Brown. Male slightly darker than female overall. With the following parts black: head, pronotal callosity, femur and tarsal claws (female lighter), posterior pronotal process apical half except tip. Forewing veins brown with black on a few veins, pattern black, and brown brindle, with indistinct transverse white medial band; female with more extensive brown markings than male (
<figureCitation box="[1194,1261,300,326]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[189,232,1920,1946]" captionTargetBox="[216,1370,265,1881]" captionTargetId="figure-12@4.[216,1370,265,1881]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 1. Machaerotypus stigmosus Li &amp; Chen sp. nov. A, C, E. Paratype, ♀ (IEGU), habitus in dorsal, frontal and lateral view. B, D, F. Paratype, ♂ (IEGU), habitus in dorsal, frontal and lateral view. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6761663" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6761663/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="72">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). Abdomen black, with base of each segment narrowly yellow-white.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6761671" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6761671" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6761671/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="71" startId="7.[189,232,1920,1946]" targetBox="[194,1395,633,1809]" targetPageId="7">
<paragraph blockId="7.[188,1398,1920,2017]" pageId="7" pageNumber="71">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,267,1920,1946]" pageId="7" pageNumber="71">Fig. 4.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Li &amp; Chen" authorityName="Li &amp; Chen" authorityYear="2022" box="[272,707,1920,1947]" class="Insecta" family="Membracidae" genus="Machaerotypus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stigmosus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[272,576,1920,1946]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="71">Machaerotypus stigmosus</emphasis>
Li &amp; Chen
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[714,806,1921,1947]" pageId="7" pageNumber="71" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, paratype, ♀ (IEGU). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1064,1119,1920,1946]" pageId="7" pageNumber="71">A–B</emphasis>
. Genitalia in lateral and ventral view. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[353,372,1955,1981]" pageId="7" pageNumber="71">C</emphasis>
. Sternite VII, ventral view. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[709,728,1956,1982]" pageId="7" pageNumber="71">D</emphasis>
. First valvulae, lateral view. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1080,1098,1956,1982]" pageId="7" pageNumber="71">E</emphasis>
. Second valvulae, lateral view. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[259,277,1991,2017]" pageId="7" pageNumber="71">F</emphasis>
. Third valvulae (gonoplac), lateral view. Scale bars = 0.2 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="8.[188,1400,401,674]" pageId="8" pageNumber="72">
HEAD AND THORAX. Vertex with dorsal margin trapezoidal, ocelli slightly closer to inner margin of eyes than to each other; frontoclypeus more than two-thirds length of vertex ventral margins, apex expanded (
<figureCitation box="[197,329,471,497]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[189,232,1920,1946]" captionTargetBox="[216,1370,265,1881]" captionTargetId="figure-12@4.[216,1370,265,1881]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 1. Machaerotypus stigmosus Li &amp; Chen sp. nov. A, C, E. Paratype, ♀ (IEGU), habitus in dorsal, frontal and lateral view. B, D, F. Paratype, ♂ (IEGU), habitus in dorsal, frontal and lateral view. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6761663" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6761663/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="72">Fig. 1C–D</figureCitation>
), frontoclypeal lobes distinct, length more than half as long as frontoclypeus. Pronotum with punctures evenly distributed. Callosity nearly triangular, with sparse setae, surface smooth. Suprahumeral horns short. Posterior pronotal process ending at anal angle of forewing at rest, depressed at base, strongly expanded near middle in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[850,974,577,603]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[189,232,1920,1946]" captionTargetBox="[216,1370,265,1881]" captionTargetId="figure-12@4.[216,1370,265,1881]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 1. Machaerotypus stigmosus Li &amp; Chen sp. nov. A, C, E. Paratype, ♀ (IEGU), habitus in dorsal, frontal and lateral view. B, D, F. Paratype, ♂ (IEGU), habitus in dorsal, frontal and lateral view. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6761663" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6761663/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="72">Fig. 1E–F</figureCitation>
). Basal fourth of forewing punctate with opaque sclerotization, veins M and Cu fused on the first brown brindle area, veins M+Cu and R fused at center of opaque sclerotization (
<figureCitation box="[665,794,647,673]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[189,232,1952,1978]" captionTargetBox="[218,1363,278,1913]" captionTargetId="figure-14@5.[205,1382,265,1913]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig. 2. Machaerotypus stigmosus Li &amp; Chen sp. nov. A. Paratype, ♂ (IEGU), forewing. B. Paratype, ♀ (IEGU), forewing. C. Paratype, ♀ (IEGU), hind wing. Scale bars: A–C = 0.5 mm. a–e = white parts." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6761667" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6761667/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="72">Fig. 2A–B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[188,1399,713,915]" pageId="8" pageNumber="72">
MALE GENITALIA. Pygofer with dorsal margin slightly convex in lateral view, sternite IX longer than wide in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[381,479,748,774]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="6.[189,232,1922,1948]" captionTargetBox="[216,1365,268,1883]" captionTargetId="figure-11@6.[216,1371,265,1883]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Fig. 3. Machaerotypus stigmosus Li &amp; Chen sp. nov., paratype, ♂ (IEGU). A, C, D. Genitalia in lateral, posterior and ventral view. B, E. Aedeagus, posterior and lateral view. F. Style, dorsal view. G. Lateral plate. Scale bars = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6761669" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6761669/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="72">Fig. 3A</figureCitation>
). Lateral plate upper half narrow and pointed, depressed slightly on bottom half, with setae on margin (
<figureCitation box="[515,610,783,809]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="6.[189,232,1922,1948]" captionTargetBox="[216,1365,268,1883]" captionTargetId="figure-11@6.[216,1371,265,1883]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Fig. 3. Machaerotypus stigmosus Li &amp; Chen sp. nov., paratype, ♂ (IEGU). A, C, D. Genitalia in lateral, posterior and ventral view. B, E. Aedeagus, posterior and lateral view. F. Style, dorsal view. G. Lateral plate. Scale bars = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6761669" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6761669/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="72">Fig. 3G</figureCitation>
). Basal half of subgenital plate fused (
<figureCitation box="[1066,1161,783,809]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="6.[189,232,1922,1948]" captionTargetBox="[216,1365,268,1883]" captionTargetId="figure-11@6.[216,1371,265,1883]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Fig. 3. Machaerotypus stigmosus Li &amp; Chen sp. nov., paratype, ♂ (IEGU). A, C, D. Genitalia in lateral, posterior and ventral view. B, E. Aedeagus, posterior and lateral view. F. Style, dorsal view. G. Lateral plate. Scale bars = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6761669" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6761669/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="72">Fig. 3D</figureCitation>
). Style clasp angled dorsally; distally recurved, distal half slender, dorsal surface with setae; connective n-shaped (
<figureCitation captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="6.[189,232,1922,1948]" captionTargetBox="[216,1365,268,1883]" captionTargetId="figure-11@6.[216,1371,265,1883]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Fig. 3. Machaerotypus stigmosus Li &amp; Chen sp. nov., paratype, ♂ (IEGU). A, C, D. Genitalia in lateral, posterior and ventral view. B, E. Aedeagus, posterior and lateral view. F. Style, dorsal view. G. Lateral plate. Scale bars = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6761669" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6761669/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="72">Fig. 3A, F</figureCitation>
). Aedeagus in lateral view U-shaped, shaft with slight convexity near base, tapered distally with coarse denticles in distal half of dorsal margin; gonopore oblong, preapical on posterior surface (
<figureCitation box="[1240,1366,889,915]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="6.[189,232,1922,1948]" captionTargetBox="[216,1365,268,1883]" captionTargetId="figure-11@6.[216,1371,265,1883]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Fig. 3. Machaerotypus stigmosus Li &amp; Chen sp. nov., paratype, ♂ (IEGU). A, C, D. Genitalia in lateral, posterior and ventral view. B, E. Aedeagus, posterior and lateral view. F. Style, dorsal view. G. Lateral plate. Scale bars = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6761669" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6761669/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="72">Fig. 3B, E</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[189,1399,954,1157]" pageId="8" pageNumber="72">
FEMALE GENITALIA. Sternite VII in ventral view with posterior margin deeply concave, both sides with setae (
<figureCitation box="[267,360,989,1015]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="7.[189,232,1920,1946]" captionTargetBox="[194,1395,633,1809]" captionTargetId="figure-104@7.[189,1398,621,1881]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Fig. 4. Machaerotypus stigmosus Li &amp; Chen sp. nov., paratype, ♀ (IEGU). A–B. Genitalia in lateral and ventral view. C. Sternite VII, ventral view. D. First valvulae, lateral view. E. Second valvulae, lateral view. F. Third valvulae (gonoplac), lateral view. Scale bars = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6761671" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6761671/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="72">Fig. 4C</figureCitation>
). Pygofer longer than wide in lateral view with numerous setae; drop-shaped in ventral view (
<figureCitation box="[268,402,1024,1051]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="7.[189,232,1920,1946]" captionTargetBox="[194,1395,633,1809]" captionTargetId="figure-104@7.[189,1398,621,1881]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Fig. 4. Machaerotypus stigmosus Li &amp; Chen sp. nov., paratype, ♀ (IEGU). A–B. Genitalia in lateral and ventral view. C. Sternite VII, ventral view. D. First valvulae, lateral view. E. Second valvulae, lateral view. F. Third valvulae (gonoplac), lateral view. Scale bars = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6761671" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6761671/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="72">Fig. 4A–B</figureCitation>
). First valvulae gradually narrowed and tapered to acute apex (
<figureCitation box="[1189,1289,1024,1051]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="7.[189,232,1920,1946]" captionTargetBox="[194,1395,633,1809]" captionTargetId="figure-104@7.[189,1398,621,1881]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Fig. 4. Machaerotypus stigmosus Li &amp; Chen sp. nov., paratype, ♀ (IEGU). A–B. Genitalia in lateral and ventral view. C. Sternite VII, ventral view. D. First valvulae, lateral view. E. Second valvulae, lateral view. F. Third valvulae (gonoplac), lateral view. Scale bars = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6761671" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6761671/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="72">Fig. 4D</figureCitation>
). Second valvulae gradually widened from base to near midlength with slight dorsal hump near base, distal half of dorsal margin irregularly and finely dentate, apex bluntly pointed (
<figureCitation box="[988,1077,1095,1121]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="7.[189,232,1920,1946]" captionTargetBox="[194,1395,633,1809]" captionTargetId="figure-104@7.[189,1398,621,1881]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Fig. 4. Machaerotypus stigmosus Li &amp; Chen sp. nov., paratype, ♀ (IEGU). A–B. Genitalia in lateral and ventral view. C. Sternite VII, ventral view. D. First valvulae, lateral view. E. Second valvulae, lateral view. F. Third valvulae (gonoplac), lateral view. Scale bars = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6761671" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6761671/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="72">Fig. 4E</figureCitation>
). Third valvulae (gonoplac) broadly rounded distally, ventral margin with numerous setae (
<figureCitation box="[924,1014,1130,1156]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="7.[189,232,1920,1946]" captionTargetBox="[194,1395,633,1809]" captionTargetId="figure-104@7.[189,1398,621,1881]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Fig. 4. Machaerotypus stigmosus Li &amp; Chen sp. nov., paratype, ♀ (IEGU). A–B. Genitalia in lateral and ventral view. C. Sternite VII, ventral view. D. First valvulae, lateral view. E. Second valvulae, lateral view. F. Third valvulae (gonoplac), lateral view. Scale bars = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6761671" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6761671/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="72">Fig. 4F</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
