<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="72" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="8.[189,303,1308,1334]" box="[189,303,1308,1334]" pageId="8" pageNumber="72">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,303,1308,1334]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="8" pageNumber="72" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,303,1308,1334]" pageId="8" pageNumber="72">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[187,1399,1354,1486]" pageId="8" pageNumber="72">
This species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="(Lethierry, 1876)" baseAuthorityName="Lethierry" baseAuthorityYear="1876" box="[477,825,1354,1380]" class="Insecta" family="Membracidae" genus="Machaerotypus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="72" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sibiricus">
<emphasis box="[477,616,1354,1380]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="72">M. sibiricus</emphasis>
(Lethierry, 1876)
</taxonomicName>
, but differs from the latter as follows: 1) forewing with many spots and brown wide stripe (hyaline in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Lethierry" baseAuthorityYear="1876" box="[779,918,1389,1415]" class="Insecta" family="Membracidae" genus="Machaerotypus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="72" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sibiricus">
<emphasis box="[779,918,1389,1415]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="72">M. sibiricus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); 2) posterior pronotal process depressed at base, strongly expanded near midlength (flat a base and center in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Lethierry" baseAuthorityYear="1876" box="[970,1109,1424,1450]" class="Insecta" family="Membracidae" genus="Machaerotypus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="72" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sibiricus">
<emphasis box="[970,1109,1424,1450]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="72">M. sibiricus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); 3) ocelli slightly closer to inner margin of eyes than to each other (equidistant in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Lethierry" baseAuthorityYear="1876" box="[860,1001,1460,1486]" class="Insecta" family="Membracidae" genus="Machaerotypus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="72" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sibiricus">
<emphasis box="[860,1001,1460,1486]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="72">M. sibiricus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
